ProMED-mail
e-mail: promed@usa.healthnet.org
[The reports painted a rather grim picture of the present status of the
Nipah virus encephalitis outbreak in peninsular Malaysia. There should be
no doubt that Nipah virus has already spread countrywide, at least among
pigs. At least one new yet-to-be-confirmed human case (patient is now in a
coma) has been reported. To make matter worse, military personnel have been
taken off pig culling operations, resulting in delay in culling of infected
pigs because of lack of shooters. - Mod. CYC]
[Given that wild birds are a natural amplifying host for Japanese
encephalitis virus, what will happen next mosquito season when mosquitoes,
infected by feeding on such birds, look for a mammalian vertebrate blood
meal? If there won't be any pigs around for them to feed on will they
quest for other large vertebrates, such as humans? - Mod.CC]
